================================================================================
SECTION 12 — SOFT DELETE ENFORCEMENT
================================================================================

RULE: No DELETE SQL statement may be issued against the students or courses
tables under any user-triggered code path. Deactivation sets is_active = FALSE.
The only permitted hard delete is against the enrollments table (unenrollment).

RULE: Every repository method that queries students or courses for list or
lookup operations must include a WHERE is_active = TRUE filter by default.
The base repository class must enforce this as a class-level default that
cannot be accidentally omitted.

RULE: The GET /students/{student_id} and GET /courses/{course_id} endpoints
must return 200 OK with the full record even if is_active = false. They must
return 404 only if the UUID does not exist at all. This is the inactive
resource behaviour defined in API-CONTRACTS.md sections 2.3 and 3.3.

RULE: The repository get_by_id method for students and courses must NOT apply
the is_active filter. It returns any record matching the UUID regardless of
active status. The list_paginated method applies the is_active filter.

RULE: CourseService must verify that zero rows exist in enrollments with
course_id matching the target course before setting is_active = FALSE on
that course. If any enrollment rows exist, CourseHasActiveEnrollmentsException
must be raised before any update is issued.


================================================================================
SECTION 13 — WHAT IS EXPLICITLY PROHIBITED
================================================================================

The following patterns are prohibited throughout the entire codebase.
Any code suggestion containing these patterns must be rejected.

PROHIBITED IN ROUTERS:
- Direct SQLAlchemy imports or session usage
- Repository class instantiation or method calls
- if-statements implementing business rules
- try/except blocks constructing error response dicts
- Returning raw Pydantic model instances without the envelope builder
- Returning JSONResponse(...) inline without going through envelope.py

PROHIBITED IN SERVICES:
- SQLAlchemy imports of any kind
- Direct database session references
- Hardcoded repository instantiation (use constructor injection)
- Returning HTTP status codes, dicts shaped like error envelopes, or
  JSONResponse objects
- Synchronous method definitions (all methods must be async def)

PROHIBITED IN REPOSITORIES:
- Business logic of any kind
- Raising domain exceptions other than to re-raise a caught DB constraint
  violation as the appropriate typed domain exception
- Returning raw ORM-bound objects to the service layer
- Omitting the is_active = TRUE filter on list queries for students or courses
- Synchronous method definitions (all methods must be async def)

PROHIBITED GLOBALLY:
- Hardcoded secrets, database URLs, or JWT signing keys anywhere in app/ code
  (all must come from core/config.py via environment variables)
- print() statements in any file under app/ or src/
- Raw Python Exception, ValueError, or KeyError raised to signal a domain error
- Any HTTP endpoint exposed outside the /api/v1/ prefix
- Any response that does not conform to the standard success or error envelope
- Permanent deletion of student or course records under any user-triggered path
- Logging PII: email addresses, JWT tokens, Authorization headers, passwords
- camelCase JSON field names in any API request or response body
- Client-supplied id, student_id, course_id values used as primary keys
  (all PKs are server-generated UUIDs)
- Synchronous SQLAlchemy Session (use AsyncSession only)
- localStorage or sessionStorage usage in the frontend for auth tokens
  (tokens must be managed in memory or httpOnly cookies only)


